WEBVTT

01:40.380 --> 01:48.740
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP05]

01:49.259 --> 01:50.300
Stop right there!

01:50.300 --> 01:51.220
Come and catch me!

01:54.220 --> 01:55.660
I'm sorry!

02:06.419 --> 02:08.179
Apologies, I wasn't watching them.

02:09.459 --> 02:10.100
It's... it's fine.

02:19.699 --> 02:21.139
I noticed that Cen Sisi

02:21.139 --> 02:22.660
has a lot of photos on social media

02:22.660 --> 02:23.579
that copy your look.

02:49.220 --> 02:50.180
What was on your mind?

02:52.019 --> 02:52.620
Thanks for

02:53.060 --> 02:54.340
being quick on your feet back there.

02:54.699 --> 02:55.819
I almost blew our cover.

02:58.419 --> 02:59.220
You are a natural.

03:01.299 --> 03:02.220
Well, do you think

03:02.620 --> 03:04.220
I could make it to primetime?

03:06.180 --> 03:07.259
Good enough to fool amateurs.

03:09.100 --> 03:10.739
[Meaning... he's no amateur himself.]

03:11.299 --> 03:12.979
[Did I just make myself a joke in front of him?]

03:17.900 --> 03:18.500
Chen Hui.

03:18.819 --> 03:20.180
Give Miss Ruan a ride in a bit.

03:20.460 --> 03:21.419
Make sure to send Mr. Liu

03:21.419 --> 03:22.060
a backup recording.

03:22.620 --> 03:23.019
Got it.

03:23.660 --> 03:25.259
Mr. Xu, aren't you heading back to the firm?

03:25.819 --> 03:27.180
No, I'm heading to the airport.

03:28.739 --> 03:30.460
You're flying back to the States right now?

03:34.259 --> 03:34.900
So you...

03:36.019 --> 03:37.060
you came all this way

03:37.060 --> 03:38.579
just for my case?

03:41.460 --> 03:42.819
Do you think, Miss Ruan, that I

03:43.579 --> 03:44.739
have nothing better to do?

03:51.620 --> 03:53.340
Thank you so much for

03:53.340 --> 03:54.579
coming with me today.

03:55.539 --> 03:56.500
You must be up to your ears.

03:57.060 --> 03:57.819
Take care of yourself.

04:00.660 --> 04:01.620
Drive safe!

04:17.019 --> 04:17.699
"Hey, just wanna tell you"

04:18.180 --> 04:19.579
"that I lost it back there."

04:19.940 --> 04:21.180
"I didn't mean what I said."

04:21.940 --> 04:23.380
"I didn't do any of those things."

04:24.179 --> 04:25.499
"Are you still around Nanhu?"

04:26.580 --> 04:28.179
She just figured out about being recorded.

04:28.419 --> 04:29.220
Nice try.

04:34.900 --> 04:35.539
"Not around."

04:35.939 --> 04:37.260
"We'll see each other in court."

05:04.499 --> 05:05.140
Coming!

05:07.100 --> 05:07.619
Hello.

05:07.939 --> 05:09.499
Hello, Mr. Xu.

05:10.179 --> 05:11.379
It's for you.

05:11.859 --> 05:13.179
Flowers for me?

05:13.299 --> 05:14.820
These are the flowers that you ordered.

05:15.100 --> 05:17.460
And don't worry. The payment's already been made.

05:19.539 --> 05:20.900
Can I help you move in?

05:20.900 --> 05:22.059
Sorry, no.

05:24.739 --> 05:25.900
What's the problem?

05:26.539 --> 05:27.900
I just really don't need that.

05:28.179 --> 05:29.299
And do me a favor

05:29.299 --> 05:30.299
just throw them out.

05:30.539 --> 05:31.499
No need?

05:34.499 --> 05:35.140
Thank you.

05:36.100 --> 05:36.900
Okay.

05:37.100 --> 05:37.460
Bye!

05:37.460 --> 05:38.419
Bye-bye, bye-bye!

05:50.179 --> 05:50.739
Hello?

05:51.179 --> 05:51.900
I didn't give you

05:51.900 --> 05:53.100
my address so you could

05:53.100 --> 05:54.140
cram my place with useless stuff.

05:54.539 --> 05:55.539
What stuff?

05:55.939 --> 05:57.340
A hideous plant.

05:59.619 --> 06:00.340
Hideous?

06:01.100 --> 06:01.979
Ruan Yu picked it out

06:01.979 --> 06:03.220
as a gesture of gratitude.

06:03.419 --> 06:04.179
I figured

06:04.179 --> 06:05.820
bringing a little life into your place

06:05.820 --> 06:06.859
wasn't such a bad idea.

06:08.419 --> 06:09.020
And besides...

06:11.780 --> 06:13.419
Sir, excuse me, sir?

06:15.539 --> 06:16.140
I'm sorry.

06:16.299 --> 06:17.939
Can you bring the flowers back to me?

06:18.539 --> 06:19.379
Why?

06:23.220 --> 06:23.900
Thank you.

06:26.340 --> 06:27.299
Fine, no why.

06:28.140 --> 06:28.539
Bye-bye!

06:28.539 --> 06:29.059
Bye.

06:33.140 --> 06:33.780
That was very

06:33.780 --> 06:34.539
generous.

06:34.539 --> 06:35.619
Did you return the favor?

06:36.460 --> 06:37.499
Of course I did!

06:42.700 --> 06:44.539
See? I sent him flowers.

06:44.820 --> 06:45.619
He just signed for them.

06:46.939 --> 06:47.939
I knew it.

06:47.939 --> 06:49.059
Romantic novelists

06:49.059 --> 06:50.179
special in "L'amour".

06:50.700 --> 06:51.539
What kind of flowers?

06:52.379 --> 06:54.179
Was it Cappuccino roses,

06:54.179 --> 06:55.700
or Blue Enchantress?

06:56.739 --> 06:57.619
Carola's nice too.

06:59.539 --> 07:00.340
Widow's-thrill.

07:02.379 --> 07:03.580
Clears heat and detoxifies,

07:03.580 --> 07:04.820
calms the mind and sharpens focus,

07:04.820 --> 07:05.820
and helps with sleep.

07:06.059 --> 07:06.539
He's always

07:06.539 --> 07:07.939
flying back and forth.

07:08.299 --> 07:09.619
Helps him with jet lag.

07:09.939 --> 07:10.900
Perfect for him.

07:14.340 --> 07:15.299
Going the practical route, huh?

07:15.900 --> 07:16.780
Nothing wrong with that.

07:17.739 --> 07:20.179
Was it just for him, or...?

07:23.619 --> 07:24.660
Easy, take it slow.

07:24.660 --> 07:25.660
It's not that heavy.

07:26.020 --> 07:26.859
Where does this go?

07:26.859 --> 07:27.419
Over there.

07:27.580 --> 07:28.499
Okay, this corner.

07:28.499 --> 07:29.539
That corner, right?

07:29.660 --> 07:30.739
What about the one from before?

07:40.460 --> 07:40.939
"Thank you."

07:46.179 --> 07:47.220
"My pleasure, Mr. Xu."

07:50.220 --> 07:51.020
"I'm putting together"

07:51.020 --> 07:52.059
"the rest of the materials."

07:52.499 --> 07:54.059
"I might need your help again when I'm done."

07:57.020 --> 07:57.979
"Don't mention it."

08:20.340 --> 08:21.059
Grumpy fluff

08:21.059 --> 08:22.020
needs me in the office.

08:22.900 --> 08:24.379
No idea what kind of meltdown awaits.

08:28.700 --> 08:30.340
Thank you, Miss Ruan,

08:30.340 --> 08:31.379
for the money tree.

08:38.780 --> 08:40.139
"What were you gonna say just now?"

08:40.700 --> 08:41.499
"'Besides...' what?"

08:43.659 --> 08:44.540
"I meant that Ruan Yu"

08:44.540 --> 08:45.859
"ordered one for each of us."

08:46.180 --> 08:47.460
"Couldn't exactly leave you out, could she?"

09:33.340 --> 09:34.100
Terminate the contract?

09:34.659 --> 09:35.259
You mean

09:35.259 --> 09:36.019
we're dropping

09:36.019 --> 09:37.259
Lily Vale's new book?

09:37.580 --> 09:38.700
Do you have any idea

09:38.700 --> 09:39.659
how many people have been

09:39.820 --> 09:41.340
trashing us on our official page?

09:42.180 --> 09:43.180
Accusing us of publishing

09:43.180 --> 09:44.340
plagiarized work.

09:44.659 --> 09:45.379
Shameless, they say.

09:45.940 --> 09:46.700
Haven't we

09:46.700 --> 09:47.220
already

09:47.220 --> 09:48.259
cleared that up?

09:48.540 --> 09:50.739
The Poet herself set the record straight.

09:50.859 --> 09:52.019
It's been Su Cheng

09:52.019 --> 09:52.820
stirring up drama,

09:52.820 --> 09:53.899
smearing Lily Vale's name.

09:54.340 --> 09:55.659
When there's public outrage,

09:56.019 --> 09:57.100
does truth really matter?

09:57.100 --> 09:58.139
Of course it does!

09:58.379 --> 09:59.060
Otherwise,

09:59.060 --> 10:00.139
what's the law even for?

10:00.499 --> 10:01.340
All this backlash

10:01.340 --> 10:02.779
was intended upon by Su Cheng.

10:02.779 --> 10:04.460
Lily Vale is taking her to court.

10:04.540 --> 10:05.820
The truth will out soon enough.

10:06.060 --> 10:07.580
Let me be clear:

10:07.859 --> 10:08.979
within three days,

10:09.100 --> 10:10.420
if this plagiarism scandal

10:10.420 --> 10:11.300
hasn't blown over,

10:11.540 --> 10:12.540
we will end

10:12.540 --> 10:14.700
all partnerships with Lily Vale.

10:14.700 --> 10:16.180
Dropping Lily Vale at this point

10:16.180 --> 10:17.580
is siding with Su Cheng.

10:17.580 --> 10:18.340
That would destroy...

10:18.340 --> 10:19.619
You'd better know when to stop.

10:21.340 --> 10:23.659
I know she's a friend of yours, and that's why

10:23.659 --> 10:24.859
you're taking her side.

10:25.379 --> 10:26.580
But get this straight:

10:26.779 --> 10:28.499
it's Liwen that pays your salary,

10:28.499 --> 10:29.460
not Lily Vale.

10:34.420 --> 10:36.180
If you want to talk about salaries...

10:37.619 --> 10:39.220
When I first joined Liwen,

10:39.899 --> 10:41.820
I was given absolutely nothing to work with.

10:43.300 --> 10:44.499
Every author I believed in...

10:44.499 --> 10:45.940
The moment they showed any promise,

10:45.940 --> 10:47.420
another editor would poach them.

10:50.700 --> 10:51.739
It was Lily Vale who handed me

10:52.619 --> 10:54.100
a manuscript everyone wanted

10:54.100 --> 10:54.940
and said, "It's yours."

10:55.180 --> 10:56.499
She trusted me completely.

10:57.979 --> 10:59.139
She's not just a friend,

10:59.700 --> 11:00.619
nor just a classmate.

11:01.420 --> 11:02.659
She is the best partner

11:02.659 --> 11:03.739
I've ever had in my career.

11:05.180 --> 11:05.979
Without her,

11:06.340 --> 11:06.820
I would've

11:06.820 --> 11:07.820
washed out of this industry.

11:10.779 --> 11:12.220
If I recall correctly,

11:13.139 --> 11:14.499
you didn't get to where you are today

11:14.859 --> 11:16.659
without Lily Vale's help either.

11:20.659 --> 11:22.100
Yet here you are, losing all your senses,

11:22.100 --> 11:23.019
burning bridges once across.

11:23.619 --> 11:25.379
who'd ever want to work with us again?

11:27.379 --> 11:28.460
Shen Mingying!

11:28.979 --> 11:30.899
You'd better watch what you say.

11:31.619 --> 11:33.060
Don't make yourself a target.

11:34.540 --> 11:35.340
If being a target

11:35.340 --> 11:36.859
means protection for Lily Vale,

11:37.739 --> 11:38.700
this will be a role

11:41.420 --> 11:42.259
gladly taken.

12:01.060 --> 12:02.379
"The recording can only serve as"

12:02.379 --> 12:03.220
"supplementary evidence."

12:03.779 --> 12:05.540
"But the side-by-side analysis we initiated"

12:05.899 --> 12:07.180
"can establish the originality"

12:07.180 --> 12:08.100
"of your novel."

12:08.859 --> 12:10.779
"Let's keep working through that."

12:11.940 --> 12:12.659
"On it."

12:58.859 --> 12:59.659
Mr. Xu,

12:59.899 --> 13:00.580
all set with

13:00.580 --> 13:01.580
Chapter Thirteen.

13:01.820 --> 13:03.139
I'll go over it again tonight.

13:08.139 --> 13:09.220
Sorry, I have to take this.

13:11.180 --> 13:11.779
Hello?

13:13.700 --> 13:14.379
At home.

13:17.060 --> 13:17.859
Can't rule out retaliation

13:17.859 --> 13:18.940
from the defendant.

13:19.420 --> 13:20.300
SG's top brass

13:20.300 --> 13:21.540
should know better than anyone.

13:22.019 --> 13:22.820
The defendant is

13:22.820 --> 13:24.580
capable of remotely detonating a bomb.

13:34.499 --> 13:35.700
That's a matter for the police.

13:37.460 --> 13:39.060
Alright, handle it on your end.

13:45.259 --> 13:45.859
Sorry about that.

13:49.139 --> 13:49.820
Mr. Xu,

13:50.220 --> 13:51.859
isn't it pretty late where you are?

13:55.420 --> 13:57.379
Wasn't the caffeine doing the job?

14:16.540 --> 14:17.580
What did you just say?

14:19.899 --> 14:21.859
I was asking if it's too late on your end.

14:21.859 --> 14:23.340
Are you okay to keep going?

14:27.060 --> 14:27.739
Yeah, let's go.

14:37.899 --> 14:40.420
Let's move on to Chapter Fourteen.

14:51.499 --> 14:54.300
Chapter Fourteen, paragraph three.

14:57.899 --> 14:58.859
He had never

14:58.859 --> 15:00.340
been fond of fuzzy animals.

15:01.180 --> 15:02.940
Until the day he passed by the art museum

15:03.820 --> 15:05.019
and saw her crouched in the bushes,

15:05.180 --> 15:06.259
feeding a stray cat.

15:07.460 --> 15:09.259
Sunlight. A gentle breeze.

15:09.779 --> 15:11.779
Green grass. A cat.

15:12.460 --> 15:13.139
And her.

15:14.220 --> 15:15.100
Taken together,

15:15.460 --> 15:16.379
a sight of tenderness

15:16.379 --> 15:17.700
just short of heartbroken.

15:18.300 --> 15:19.420
Softly, it landed right in his chest.

15:20.379 --> 15:21.139
From that day on,

15:21.700 --> 15:23.100
as if contagious with this love,

15:24.139 --> 15:25.580
he began doing what she did —

15:26.300 --> 15:27.779
saying hi to every fluffy

15:27.779 --> 15:28.540
on campus.

15:29.659 --> 15:30.619
Yet somehow,

15:31.499 --> 15:33.180
he could never manage to say that same word

15:33.859 --> 15:34.220
to her.

15:44.779 --> 15:46.580
He is a cat person after all.

15:47.180 --> 15:48.180
I must've lost my mind

15:48.180 --> 15:49.259
tweaking his persona like that.

15:54.300 --> 15:55.220
These two lines match

15:55.220 --> 15:56.619
pretty much word for word.

15:57.979 --> 15:58.619
Mr. Xu,

15:59.060 --> 16:00.100
what's your take on this?

16:01.340 --> 16:02.379
I think there are still some

16:02.379 --> 16:03.340
subtle differences.

16:03.700 --> 16:05.220
You meant your male lead to love cats to the extent

16:05.220 --> 16:06.139
that the female lead does.

16:06.739 --> 16:08.499
But in the other work, it isn't.

16:19.499 --> 16:20.300
I see it now.

16:20.779 --> 16:21.940
The Poet's male lead was well aware

16:21.940 --> 16:22.700
when the female lead

16:22.700 --> 16:23.739
would pass by the art museum

16:24.060 --> 16:25.379
and staged the whole thing.

16:25.379 --> 16:26.180
So it's not a case

16:26.180 --> 16:27.060
of love spilling over.

16:29.659 --> 16:30.779
I was reading it with assumptions.

16:31.139 --> 16:32.100
I forgot she'd rewritten him

16:32.100 --> 16:33.259
as a calculating type.

16:35.940 --> 16:36.859
"Calculating"...

16:37.820 --> 16:38.739
... is a negative word, isn't it?

16:42.739 --> 16:43.300
Not really.

16:43.820 --> 16:45.540
Mr. Xu, don't get the wrong idea again.

16:45.540 --> 16:46.700
I'm not criticizing the male lead.

16:47.420 --> 16:48.379
I'm being completely

16:48.379 --> 16:49.899
rational in this analysis.

16:50.460 --> 16:51.259
"Calculating"...

16:52.460 --> 16:54.300
It's more of a neutral term, really.

16:54.899 --> 16:55.820
On the positive side,

16:55.820 --> 16:57.619
it just means the guy is clever.

17:09.019 --> 17:10.300
Is that coffee still hot?

17:10.300 --> 17:11.460
Is he or she okay

17:11.460 --> 17:12.139
over there?

17:13.300 --> 17:13.859
It's not hot.

17:16.300 --> 17:16.820
Come here.

17:20.219 --> 17:22.219
How old is your cat?

17:22.540 --> 17:23.699
Fully vaccinated?

17:24.139 --> 17:25.260
Okay to bathe right now?

17:25.699 --> 17:26.820
All vaccinations are done.

17:27.340 --> 17:28.980
About six months old.

17:30.500 --> 17:31.179
Okay then,

17:31.179 --> 17:32.459
you should give he or she a wash.

17:32.859 --> 17:33.619
If the little one

17:33.619 --> 17:34.780
licked up some of the residue,

17:34.780 --> 17:35.859
it could be harmful.

17:36.139 --> 17:36.939
We can resume

17:36.939 --> 17:37.540
in a bit.

17:38.100 --> 17:38.659
Alright.

17:45.939 --> 17:46.740
How do I do it?

17:47.459 --> 17:48.219
You don't know how?

17:51.939 --> 17:53.060
Isn't it your cat?

17:56.500 --> 17:58.659
Then whose cat is staying with him?

18:01.100 --> 18:01.740
So, how?

18:04.580 --> 18:06.980
You'll need cat shampoo,

18:07.740 --> 18:08.659
an absorbent towel,

18:09.100 --> 18:10.219
and ideally a dryer too.

18:10.699 --> 18:12.260
Then place the cat in the tub

18:12.260 --> 18:13.500
or the sink. Either works.

18:13.699 --> 18:14.780
Use water between

18:14.780 --> 18:15.899
38 and 40 degrees.

18:16.060 --> 18:16.859
- Make sure...
- Wait.

18:32.580 --> 18:33.619
What do I do now?

18:33.859 --> 18:35.179
First, adjust the temperature.

18:35.459 --> 18:35.820
Do not

18:35.820 --> 18:37.219
spray with the showerhead.

18:37.740 --> 18:39.659
Fill the tub first.

18:39.899 --> 18:41.340
Keep the water level nice and shallow.

18:45.699 --> 18:46.740
Looks like the kitten's frightened.

18:46.939 --> 18:48.459
Be gentle with your movements.

18:56.340 --> 18:57.379
What do I do next?

18:57.540 --> 18:58.540
With your left hand,

18:58.540 --> 18:59.540
hold it gently by the scruff.

18:59.899 --> 19:01.179
Don't grip too hard.

19:09.619 --> 19:10.260
And then?

19:10.859 --> 19:12.260
Wet your fingers of the other hand,

19:12.540 --> 19:13.619
[Little by little, dampen everything]

19:13.619 --> 19:14.179
[below its neck]

19:14.179 --> 19:15.340
[before applying the shampoo.]

19:17.659 --> 19:19.219
[Make sure not to get water in its nose or mouth.]

20:33.619 --> 20:34.340
All clean.

20:37.179 --> 20:37.740
Good.

20:38.060 --> 20:38.859
Mr. Xu,

20:38.859 --> 20:40.340
take that absorbent towel

20:40.340 --> 20:41.260
and pat it dry,

20:41.260 --> 20:42.619
then put it in the dryer.

20:43.020 --> 20:44.020
Be gentle when you pat,

20:44.379 --> 20:45.540
and turn the dryer

20:45.540 --> 20:46.219
down low.

21:46.619 --> 21:47.980
[So he likes cats too.]

21:49.899 --> 21:50.500
That's sweet.

22:34.740 --> 22:35.699
Mr. Xu...

22:35.699 --> 22:37.060
I... I'm still here!

22:44.939 --> 22:45.580
Oh, I forgot.

22:55.859 --> 22:56.659
I need to shower.

22:58.899 --> 23:00.699
So, uh, Mr. Xu...

23:01.219 --> 23:02.340
Could you move me... I mean...

23:02.820 --> 23:03.540
Uh... Can you take

23:03.540 --> 23:04.780
the laptop out of the room?

23:05.179 --> 23:06.260
Can't you just end the video call?

23:07.899 --> 23:08.260
Right.

23:08.699 --> 23:09.260
Right, right, right.

23:10.100 --> 23:10.899
I, uh, I...

23:15.740 --> 23:17.580
Oh my god! A shirtless man!

23:18.060 --> 23:19.340
You scared me to death!

23:20.340 --> 23:21.459
Xu Huaisong?

23:22.859 --> 23:23.500
What?

23:23.820 --> 23:24.459
That's my question.

23:24.580 --> 23:25.300
What's going on just now?

23:25.659 --> 23:26.020
I...

23:26.020 --> 23:26.939
Spill it. Now.

23:28.060 --> 23:29.619
What is there to spill?

23:30.580 --> 23:31.340
His cat

23:31.340 --> 23:33.020
knocked coffee all over him.

23:33.020 --> 23:34.419
And he's awful at bathing cats,

23:35.459 --> 23:36.980
so he got soaked too.

23:37.500 --> 23:38.219
That's the scene

23:38.219 --> 23:39.139
you just walked in on.

23:43.219 --> 23:44.020
Wait, wait, wait.

23:44.659 --> 23:45.139
Something doesn't add up.

23:46.659 --> 23:47.219
Like what?

23:48.740 --> 23:50.459
First, he has a cat.

23:50.780 --> 23:51.820
Second, he has a cat but

23:51.820 --> 23:52.780
doesn't know how to bathe it.

23:52.780 --> 23:53.699
So who's the one

23:53.699 --> 23:54.580
that normally does it?

23:54.859 --> 23:55.659
Are you saying that

23:57.020 --> 23:58.379
there's someone else living with him?

24:00.659 --> 24:01.619
That he has a girlfriend?

24:03.139 --> 24:04.219
Or maybe he usually just

24:04.219 --> 24:05.580
takes the cat to a groomer.

24:05.580 --> 24:06.899
But your hypothesis is

24:06.899 --> 24:07.780
not that far-fetched.

24:09.980 --> 24:10.699
True.

24:12.219 --> 24:13.859
He has a dryer at home.

24:14.540 --> 24:15.219
So someone

24:15.219 --> 24:17.060
probably has been bathing that cat at home.

24:20.219 --> 24:20.699
Besides,

24:20.699 --> 24:21.980
he's not exactly young anymore.

24:21.980 --> 24:22.980
Accomplished guys like that

24:23.619 --> 24:25.139
hardly stay single.

24:25.580 --> 24:26.659
Oh, actually, I have news.

24:26.659 --> 24:27.340
I almost forgot.

24:27.459 --> 24:28.100
Good news.

24:28.899 --> 24:30.179
The official account for Qianhe

24:30.179 --> 24:31.300
just put out a statement,

24:31.980 --> 24:34.300
concluding that a thorough investigation has led to

24:34.619 --> 24:35.619
The Poet's confession

24:35.980 --> 24:37.580
that they weren't the original author,

24:37.980 --> 24:38.899
Su Cheng's accusations

24:38.899 --> 24:40.780
are proven groundless.

24:40.780 --> 24:41.939
So it's officially confirmed

24:42.179 --> 24:44.100
you are 100%

24:44.100 --> 24:45.899
the original author.

24:45.899 --> 24:46.699
I sent you the link.

24:46.699 --> 24:47.340
Take a look.

24:49.219 --> 24:50.340
I totally missed it just now.

24:51.340 --> 24:52.100
"Please check out"

24:52.419 --> 24:53.219
"the official statement from Qianhe."

24:53.219 --> 24:54.100
"Could this be used"

24:54.699 --> 24:55.899
"as supporting evidence"

24:55.899 --> 24:56.740
"in court?"

24:56.740 --> 24:57.699
You should've seen

24:57.699 --> 24:59.340
the look on our editor-in-chief's face.

25:00.179 --> 25:01.100
Yesterday she was

25:01.260 --> 25:02.580
rattling on and on

25:02.580 --> 25:03.419
like a machine gun.

25:03.419 --> 25:04.060
And today?

25:04.379 --> 25:05.139
On seeing the statement,

25:05.139 --> 25:06.780
she did a complete 180.

25:06.780 --> 25:07.939
Flipped faster than ever.

25:08.699 --> 25:10.500
I guess that's how you get to the top.

25:10.500 --> 25:11.659
You gotta know when to bend.

25:13.820 --> 25:15.379
Did you get into it with her again?

25:16.500 --> 25:17.060
No way.

25:17.659 --> 25:19.060
I was making a reasoned argument.

25:19.060 --> 25:20.540
She's the one who lost it.

25:22.740 --> 25:24.260
Thanks for taking that bullet for me, girl.

25:24.260 --> 25:24.859
No worries.

25:24.859 --> 25:25.980
Buy me dinner and we're even.

25:26.340 --> 25:27.300
I'll buy you so many.

25:27.419 --> 25:27.899
Deal.

25:29.580 --> 25:30.659
With this statement,

25:30.780 --> 25:32.419
our chances just got a lot better.

25:34.780 --> 25:35.820
But Cen Sisi just got

25:35.820 --> 25:37.300
publicly called out by the platform.

25:38.820 --> 25:39.859
She'll probably spin up

25:39.859 --> 25:40.740
another army of trolls.

25:41.500 --> 25:42.300
Easy-peasy.

25:42.820 --> 25:44.300
Since we can't stop people from talking,

25:44.899 --> 25:46.260
we just close our own eyes.

25:46.740 --> 25:47.619
Out of sight, out of mind.

25:54.219 --> 25:55.020
"Makes sense."

26:00.580 --> 26:01.980
We barely put the curtain up

26:02.260 --> 26:03.699
and Mr. Liu's already pulling it down.

26:04.459 --> 26:04.859
What?

26:05.179 --> 26:05.619
Look.

26:05.659 --> 26:06.500
"Throwing Su Cheng under the bus"

26:06.500 --> 26:07.540
"just to protect Lily Vale?"

26:07.540 --> 26:08.500
"Dumb move."

26:08.619 --> 26:10.219
"The milky cow wins, obviously."

26:10.459 --> 26:11.260
"TBH,"

26:11.260 --> 26:11.939
"her success"

26:11.939 --> 26:12.859
is sheer luck."

26:12.980 --> 26:14.060
"Su Cheng's way better."

26:14.219 --> 26:14.859
"This world"

26:14.859 --> 26:15.899
"shall see justice."

26:16.179 --> 26:17.580
"I'm on Su Cheng's side."

26:17.939 --> 26:18.780
"Busy?"

26:19.500 --> 26:20.100
"Not really."

26:21.500 --> 26:22.659
"Write another version."

26:23.060 --> 26:24.740
"This one barely has any punch."

26:27.100 --> 26:28.459
"I'm not a putty in your hands."

26:29.020 --> 26:30.379
"You only get one shot at a statement."

26:30.980 --> 26:32.340
"If it doesn't hit right away,"

26:32.699 --> 26:34.020
"it's as good as a total loss."

26:34.260 --> 26:35.659
"Tell me: what matters more?"

26:36.100 --> 26:37.419
"Your client's interests or your pride?"

26:38.699 --> 26:39.580
"Easier of you to say."

26:42.459 --> 26:44.540
"I'm not joking this time, Mr. Liu."

26:45.100 --> 26:47.100
"This really wasn't up to standard."

26:50.139 --> 26:51.580
"Can't argue with that."

26:51.939 --> 26:53.740
"I've been buried in cases."

26:53.740 --> 26:54.859
"What were those"

26:55.459 --> 26:56.300
"screenshots again?"

27:09.659 --> 27:11.020
"The audio evidence is locked in."

27:11.459 --> 27:13.100
"We can go head-to-head with the defendant now."

27:13.740 --> 27:14.899
"The statement"

27:14.899 --> 27:15.820
"was just the first step."

27:16.020 --> 27:17.340
"Some public pushback"

27:17.340 --> 27:18.580
"is expected."

27:18.740 --> 27:19.540
"Don't sweat."

27:19.699 --> 27:21.459
"There's a legal statement following up."

27:21.740 --> 27:22.699
"By the end of today,"

27:22.699 --> 27:24.379
"the narrative will make a U-turn."

27:25.100 --> 27:27.300
Mr. Liu really doesn't seem to be cutting it.

27:28.740 --> 27:30.179
Is he even reliable?

27:31.179 --> 27:31.740
On that front,

27:31.740 --> 27:34.260
I'd say no one beats Mr. Xu.

27:34.939 --> 27:35.899
But it seems like he's

27:35.899 --> 27:36.939
already taken.

27:37.260 --> 27:38.379
The way he texts you

27:38.379 --> 27:39.419
is so formal it hurts.

27:43.419 --> 27:44.100
Well then,

27:46.300 --> 27:48.300
Well, I'll put on my diplomatic mask too.

27:49.580 --> 27:50.300
"Alright."

27:50.419 --> 27:51.419
"Mr. Xu,"

27:51.540 --> 27:53.100
"I can't thank you enough. Both of you."

28:01.340 --> 28:02.060
"Noted."

28:10.419 --> 28:11.020
Remember

28:11.020 --> 28:12.659
back when you were serializing?

28:12.659 --> 28:14.379
People showed up passive-aggressive all the time,

28:14.699 --> 28:15.780
saying Su Cheng's writing

28:15.780 --> 28:17.219
was so much better than yours.

28:17.659 --> 28:19.260
You shrugged them away.

28:19.540 --> 28:20.699
Quote unquote "different strokes"

28:20.699 --> 28:21.500
"for different folks,"

28:21.859 --> 28:22.580
and that

28:22.580 --> 28:23.939
readers have the right to choose

28:23.939 --> 28:25.340
and leave their own opinions.

28:25.340 --> 28:26.260
In hindsight,

28:26.419 --> 28:27.980
those were never real readers.

28:27.980 --> 28:29.300
Must've been Cen Sisi's fake accounts,

28:29.300 --> 28:30.659
running her own little puppet show.

28:32.100 --> 28:33.020
Maybe.

28:33.580 --> 28:34.780
What did you even do to her

28:34.780 --> 28:36.100
to make her so obsessed with you

28:36.100 --> 28:37.060
she wouldn't let go

28:37.060 --> 28:38.820
after all these years?

28:39.340 --> 28:41.020
If only I knew.

28:44.580 --> 28:45.540
Was it about scholarship?

28:47.899 --> 28:48.939
Her recommendation spot?

28:51.580 --> 28:55.060
Don't tell me you stole her man.

28:55.060 --> 28:55.619
That can't be.

28:55.980 --> 28:57.260
You've been single since birth.

29:02.820 --> 29:03.419
Mingying.

29:04.780 --> 29:05.740
Do you think this drama

29:06.500 --> 29:08.020
has something to do with Li Shican?

29:08.540 --> 29:10.100
The way she talked about him

29:10.100 --> 29:11.939
that day at the mall...

29:12.340 --> 29:14.379
I guess she has a thing for him.

29:17.179 --> 29:18.500
Don't tell me all this trolling

29:18.500 --> 29:19.260
and copycatting

29:19.260 --> 29:21.179
was about you being her love rival?

29:22.699 --> 29:24.540
I don't have any feelings for that guy.

29:25.020 --> 29:26.300
I'm more of an

29:26.899 --> 29:28.300
imaginary rival.

29:28.699 --> 29:29.379
Spot on.

29:30.419 --> 29:31.780
Come to think of it, Cen Sisi did

29:31.780 --> 29:33.780
specifically bring up those good old days

29:33.780 --> 29:35.179
back in the arts department.

29:35.540 --> 29:36.540
With a whole lot of snark.

29:36.820 --> 29:38.219
But that was so many years ago.

29:38.780 --> 29:40.340
She can't still be hung up on it.

29:40.659 --> 29:41.540
Right?

29:42.219 --> 29:42.899
We haven't seen him

29:42.899 --> 29:43.980
in ages.

29:44.100 --> 29:45.060
And he's now

29:45.379 --> 29:47.939
a full-blown hot-shot celebrity.

30:01.179 --> 30:01.859
Hey everyone!

30:01.859 --> 30:02.820
I'm Li Shican.

30:02.820 --> 30:03.780
Thank you all so much

30:03.780 --> 30:05.219
for joining my livestream today.

30:06.020 --> 30:07.139
We just got started

30:07.139 --> 30:07.740
and I can already see

30:07.740 --> 30:08.899
our viewer count

30:08.899 --> 30:10.060
hitting a million.

30:10.340 --> 30:11.820
Looks like today's giveaways

30:11.820 --> 30:13.340
are a pretty big draw.

30:13.740 --> 30:15.100
That's right. Today,

30:15.100 --> 30:16.780
we're here to treat our "Starlights"

30:16.780 --> 30:17.699
to some special goodies.

30:18.060 --> 30:19.300
We're playing a game with Shican:

30:19.300 --> 30:20.580
Truth or Dare!

30:21.260 --> 30:21.699
Shican,

30:21.699 --> 30:23.020
good for you.

30:23.020 --> 30:24.100
Still so down-to-earth.

30:24.100 --> 30:24.780
Truth or Dare

30:24.780 --> 30:25.859
with your fans, huh?

30:25.859 --> 30:26.740
Everyone's here for it,

30:26.740 --> 30:28.699
so let's all play together!

30:28.780 --> 30:29.139
Alright!

30:29.139 --> 30:31.100
So are you brave enough to take on the challenge?

30:31.300 --> 30:31.859
Of course!

30:34.340 --> 30:35.939
The statement had barely gone out when

30:36.219 --> 30:37.340
clickbait accounts' apologies

30:37.340 --> 30:37.899
came rolling in.

30:38.540 --> 30:40.139
And all the trolls on

30:40.139 --> 30:41.060
Cen Sisi's payroll

30:41.139 --> 30:42.260
have gone quiet.

30:45.219 --> 30:47.020
Xu Huaisong really delivers.

30:48.619 --> 30:49.179
Our editor-in-chief

30:49.179 --> 30:50.139
was just nagging about

30:51.060 --> 30:52.820
how positive your image is now.

30:52.820 --> 30:54.340
Told me to push you to update

30:54.340 --> 30:55.859
and ride this wave of attention.

30:56.619 --> 30:58.020
She always has it both ways.

31:02.020 --> 31:02.659
Go on, dig in.

31:02.659 --> 31:03.899
Here's how it works:

31:03.899 --> 31:06.219
everyone can drop a comment

31:06.219 --> 31:06.899
with something

31:06.899 --> 31:08.859
you want Shican to do.

31:09.179 --> 31:10.419
If yours gets picked,

31:10.419 --> 31:11.699
Shican will not only do

31:11.699 --> 31:13.060
whatever you ask,

31:13.060 --> 31:14.179
but also throw in

31:14.179 --> 31:15.780
a signed photo.

31:18.260 --> 31:19.419
Okay, let's take a look!

31:19.859 --> 31:20.740
This one's from a fan

31:20.740 --> 31:22.859
called "Poetic Soul," who says:

31:23.540 --> 31:25.540
Shican's lucky number is seven.

31:25.619 --> 31:27.260
Can you call the seventh contact

31:27.260 --> 31:28.540
in your phonebook

31:28.540 --> 31:29.179
and say

31:29.419 --> 31:30.060
these words:

31:30.179 --> 31:32.580
"See you the day after tomorrow morning."

31:32.580 --> 31:33.340
"You know where."?

31:33.939 --> 31:35.459
That's a spicy request.

31:35.580 --> 31:37.699
Well, since it's coming from Starlights,

31:38.139 --> 31:39.060
surely Shican

31:39.060 --> 31:40.219
won't be turning it down?

31:41.300 --> 31:43.340
Of course not. Today's motto is:

31:43.340 --> 31:44.179
no request refused.

31:44.780 --> 31:45.379
My phone, please.

31:54.659 --> 31:55.619
Okay, let's listen in.

31:55.619 --> 31:56.740
Who's the lucky one

31:56.740 --> 31:58.500
on the other end of that call?

32:03.219 --> 32:04.379
This game is wild.

32:04.859 --> 32:06.300
If it were me, I'd call my mom.

32:06.419 --> 32:07.340
Always a safe bet.

32:08.300 --> 32:08.899
That's smart.

32:08.980 --> 32:10.179
You're so very quick.

32:25.820 --> 32:26.379
Me?

32:27.219 --> 32:28.060
That can't be right.

32:28.899 --> 32:29.820
Clearly it isn't

32:29.820 --> 32:30.740
his name.

32:31.260 --> 32:33.139
And your surname... "Ruan"?

32:33.699 --> 32:34.300
No way that's

32:34.300 --> 32:35.379
the seventh contact.

32:36.300 --> 32:36.899
Exactly.

32:40.340 --> 32:41.340
Just pick up.

32:48.899 --> 32:49.419
Hello?

32:49.939 --> 32:50.500
Hello.

32:53.340 --> 32:53.980
Long time no see.

32:54.300 --> 32:55.179
It's Shican.

33:07.500 --> 33:08.300
It's been a while.

33:09.100 --> 33:11.060
How have you been?

33:13.100 --> 33:13.820
Pretty good.

33:15.459 --> 33:17.500
Are you still at the same place as before?

33:20.060 --> 33:21.340
I just got back from abroad.

33:21.340 --> 33:22.340
I'd love to catch up.

33:23.179 --> 33:25.060
So let's meet up the morning

33:25.580 --> 33:26.500
after next, our usual spot.

33:28.020 --> 33:28.580
Sure.

33:29.419 --> 33:30.580
See you then. Bye!

33:34.379 --> 33:35.740
What are the odds?

33:36.139 --> 33:37.260
Talk about perfect timing.

33:37.260 --> 33:38.340
Well played, universe.

33:38.419 --> 33:39.179
Go meet up!

33:39.179 --> 33:39.619
Ask him!

33:39.619 --> 33:40.780
Ask him about Cen Sisi!

33:42.340 --> 33:43.619
The comment section is going insane!

33:45.300 --> 33:45.980
"Why does the voice"

33:45.980 --> 33:46.980
"sound so sweet?"

33:47.419 --> 33:48.020
"Baby..."

33:48.020 --> 33:49.500
"We object!"

33:50.060 --> 33:51.139
Whoever came up with that dare,

33:51.580 --> 33:52.179
well done.

33:52.179 --> 33:52.859
We have a jackpot for ya.

33:53.740 --> 33:54.300
You all always

33:54.300 --> 33:55.540
seek trouble for me.

33:57.179 --> 33:58.139
After the stream's over,

33:58.139 --> 33:58.939
remind me

33:58.939 --> 34:00.020
to go apologize to her.

34:00.020 --> 34:00.939
I can't really

34:00.939 --> 34:02.859
standing her up like that, can I?

34:04.419 --> 34:05.980
As smooth-talking as ever.

34:06.540 --> 34:08.379
Signaled in just a few words

34:08.379 --> 34:09.139
that he won't show up,

34:09.260 --> 34:10.580
just what the fans want.

34:11.060 --> 34:11.820
Impressive.

34:12.020 --> 34:12.619
So he's saying

34:12.619 --> 34:13.619
it was just the game?

34:13.619 --> 34:14.619
He wasn't actually asking you out?

34:16.179 --> 34:16.659
Fine.

34:17.259 --> 34:17.900
Then when

34:17.900 --> 34:18.819
he calls to apologize,

34:18.819 --> 34:19.819
ask him about Cen Sisi.

34:21.739 --> 34:22.980
That feels a bit awkward.

34:23.619 --> 34:24.980
We've gone so long without

34:24.980 --> 34:25.659
being in touch.

34:26.020 --> 34:27.540
How am I even supposed to start?

34:27.540 --> 34:28.380
Cringe.

34:29.299 --> 34:30.139
He has no clue about

34:30.139 --> 34:30.739
my pen name.

34:31.540 --> 34:32.420
He'd have no idea

34:32.420 --> 34:33.540
what's going on.

34:34.659 --> 34:35.619
Well, that's a wrap for today.

34:35.619 --> 34:36.580
Thanks for your hard work.

34:36.980 --> 34:37.819
Thank you, thank you!

34:38.339 --> 34:39.259
You worked hard!

34:39.259 --> 34:39.699
Shican's got

34:39.699 --> 34:41.420
bubble tea waiting for everyone

34:41.420 --> 34:42.460
in the lounge outside.

34:43.060 --> 34:43.819
Thank you all so much for today.

34:43.940 --> 34:44.779
Thank you, thank you!

34:44.779 --> 34:45.219
Xiaofei,

34:45.219 --> 34:45.739
- Lead the way.
- Thank you!

34:45.739 --> 34:46.139
Sure!

34:46.619 --> 34:47.460
This way, everyone!

34:47.580 --> 34:48.299
Let's pick up your drinks.

34:48.860 --> 34:49.460
Thanks! Bye!

34:59.020 --> 34:59.580
Shican,

35:00.779 --> 35:01.980
take a quick rest.

35:02.139 --> 35:03.020
Change your outfit.

35:03.020 --> 35:03.819
In about 15 minutes,

35:03.819 --> 35:04.739
we have another brand event.

35:06.020 --> 35:06.460
Got it.

35:10.500 --> 35:11.060
Yeah, it's over.

35:11.540 --> 35:12.779
Don't even get me started. Exhausted.

36:03.339 --> 36:04.860
Miss, this is for you.

36:06.100 --> 36:06.659
Me?

36:31.860 --> 36:33.420
Shican, absolutely perfect.

36:35.339 --> 36:35.940
Thank you.

37:05.540 --> 37:06.460
Wasn't Jingjing here

37:07.060 --> 37:08.259
the entire time?

37:08.420 --> 37:09.339
How come Director told me

37:09.339 --> 37:10.179
she stepped out,

37:10.179 --> 37:11.179
asking me to fill up for her?

37:11.540 --> 37:12.940
The director's a habitual matchmaker.

37:13.500 --> 37:14.619
There was this time when

37:14.619 --> 37:15.900
you weren't around,

37:16.460 --> 37:17.739
and he joked about you and Li Shican.

37:17.739 --> 37:19.380
A star screenwriter behind the scenes,

37:19.380 --> 37:20.619
and a male lead in front of the camera.

37:21.940 --> 37:23.699
You were made to keep it in-house.

37:24.380 --> 37:25.500
Did you notice how Li Shican was

37:25.500 --> 37:26.540
transfixed just now?

37:27.100 --> 37:28.259
Director must be shipping you.

37:29.299 --> 37:30.100
No, I...

37:30.100 --> 37:31.259
- That was just...
- Okay, look.

37:31.860 --> 37:33.380
Nobody knows you better than I do.

37:33.819 --> 37:34.900
Like I don't already know?

37:36.179 --> 37:37.699
The setting is the same as before,

37:37.900 --> 37:39.420
but a different protagonist.

37:40.819 --> 37:41.299
You weren't

37:41.299 --> 37:42.699
looking at Li Shican at all.

37:43.299 --> 37:44.860
The surroundings got to you.

37:44.860 --> 37:46.420
And a certain Mr. Xu crossed your mind again.

38:27.819 --> 38:28.779
That certain Mr. Xu...

38:31.779 --> 38:33.139
He's always the one, isn't he?

38:56.940 --> 38:57.739
"Apparently, Su Cheng"

38:57.739 --> 38:59.179
"is Lily Vale's real-life junior from school."

38:59.540 --> 39:00.420
"They had beef, which Su"

39:00.420 --> 39:01.179
"wouldn't let go of."

39:01.460 --> 39:02.940
"Waiting for the truth. #Lily Vale."

39:04.179 --> 39:04.980
"I knew it."

39:05.299 --> 39:06.940
"The Poet already cleared everything up"

39:06.940 --> 39:07.659
"and apologized."

39:07.900 --> 39:09.139
"It's a real-life grudge,"

39:09.139 --> 39:10.339
"that's why Su, a third-party, kept"

39:10.339 --> 39:11.420
"dragging Lily Vale's name"

39:11.500 --> 39:12.900
"through the mud."

39:13.619 --> 39:15.020
"This reeks of conspiracy."

39:15.659 --> 39:16.619
"What school is Su Cheng from?"

39:16.819 --> 39:17.460
"Someone pls dig into this!"

39:17.460 --> 39:18.940
Seriously? Doxxing?

39:19.980 --> 39:21.179
"Don't let yourselves be used."

39:21.420 --> 39:22.500
"Doesn't this move have a pro"

39:22.500 --> 39:23.819
"PR team written all over it?"

39:24.179 --> 39:25.619
"Lily Vale's got people working for her."

39:26.380 --> 39:27.580
What happens online, stays online.

39:28.259 --> 39:29.500
I draw my line here.

39:32.739 --> 39:33.940
"The narrative has shifted overnight."

39:34.179 --> 39:35.580
"I smell something fishy."

39:42.060 --> 39:43.980
"Mr. Xu, have you seen Weibo?"

39:49.980 --> 39:51.980
"Mr. Liu, have you seen Weibo?"

39:53.739 --> 39:54.299
"I have."

39:55.299 --> 39:57.060
"Was this your doing?"

39:57.900 --> 39:58.420
"Huh?"

39:58.860 --> 39:59.779
"No, it wasn't."

40:00.299 --> 40:01.060
"Then who?"

40:02.259 --> 40:02.819
"Not sure."

40:03.219 --> 40:04.779
"But fighting fire with fire"

40:04.779 --> 40:06.179
"is not usually our way"

40:06.420 --> 40:07.779
"of handling things."

40:08.179 --> 40:08.940
"That said,"

40:08.940 --> 40:10.179
"the defendant presumably"

40:10.179 --> 40:11.259
"thinks this was us."

40:13.259 --> 40:14.100
"Ruan Yu."

40:14.100 --> 40:15.659
"This is dirty, even for you."

40:15.940 --> 40:16.659
"If that's how it is,"

40:16.980 --> 40:18.460
"don't expect me to hold back."

40:18.699 --> 40:20.900
"Let's see who can play dirtier."

40:22.500 --> 40:23.819
Have you ever been civil with me?

40:27.219 --> 40:28.100
"The exposure"

40:28.100 --> 40:29.299
"wasn't me or my lawyers."

40:40.699 --> 40:41.500
Can't rule out retaliation

40:41.500 --> 40:42.540
from the defendant.

40:43.219 --> 40:44.060
SG's top brass should

40:44.060 --> 40:45.380
be well aware that the defendant

40:45.819 --> 40:46.619
is capable of

40:46.619 --> 40:48.259
remotely detonating explosives.

40:50.020 --> 40:51.619
With public security as solid as it is,

40:52.980 --> 40:54.659
there's no way Cen Sisi is able

40:55.819 --> 40:56.540
to pull off

40:56.540 --> 40:57.659
anything too drastic.

41:04.860 --> 41:06.940
"An incredible legend."

41:08.139 --> 41:08.900
"SG,"

41:09.819 --> 41:11.339
"hit with a baseless infringement lawsuit"

41:11.339 --> 41:12.500
"from a competitor,"

41:12.980 --> 41:14.139
"was caught in the fallout."

41:14.219 --> 41:15.020
"Stock prices cratered."

41:15.299 --> 41:16.819
"The firm is staring down a financial crisis."

41:17.619 --> 41:19.060
"Xu Yin, one of California's"

41:19.060 --> 41:20.060
"most well-regarded attorneys,"

41:20.060 --> 41:21.100
"took on the case."

41:21.619 --> 41:23.060
"Two days before the hearing,"

41:23.460 --> 41:24.420
"he suffered a sudden stroke."

41:25.299 --> 41:26.460
"After emergency treatment,"

41:26.819 --> 41:28.699
"he was diagnosed with vascular dementia."

41:29.860 --> 41:32.619
Mr. Xu is currently unconscious.

41:33.060 --> 41:34.540
What should we do about our case?

41:36.540 --> 41:37.100
This is the

41:37.100 --> 41:38.420
most critical time.

41:38.420 --> 41:40.420
And someone needs to take responsibility.

41:41.420 --> 41:42.299
You understand?

41:42.380 --> 41:44.100
If no one is responsible.

41:44.460 --> 41:47.179
I will sue your firm.

41:47.540 --> 41:48.500
Just bear with me.

41:48.500 --> 41:49.699
I don't want to bear with you.

41:51.739 --> 41:52.739
Mr. Romans,

41:53.580 --> 41:55.940
now I'm on it.

41:58.179 --> 42:00.100
"In the end, Xu Huaisong,"

42:00.460 --> 42:01.860
"Mr. Xu's son, stepped forward."

42:02.659 --> 42:03.619
"He said he had been"

42:03.619 --> 42:04.699
"studying under his father,"

42:05.219 --> 42:05.860
"had kept himself"

42:05.860 --> 42:06.819
"updated on the case"

42:06.819 --> 42:07.619
"and was ready to take over."

42:08.339 --> 42:09.299
"With the case dragging on,"

42:09.699 --> 42:11.219
"the market is projected to further dip."

42:11.860 --> 42:12.980
"At the eleventh hour, the board"

42:12.980 --> 42:13.980
"chose Xu Huaisong"

42:14.380 --> 42:15.339
"without having high hopes."

42:15.980 --> 42:17.860
"A last-minute swap is never a good sign."

42:18.900 --> 42:19.860
"But the result:"

42:21.100 --> 42:22.339
"SG won."

42:23.139 --> 42:24.500
"Mr. Xu Jr., on his own,"

42:25.299 --> 42:27.940
"brought SG back from the brink."

44:13.580 --> 44:14.380
She could be here anytime.

44:22.980 --> 44:23.380
Good girl.

44:24.219 --> 44:25.020
Stay with me a little longer.

44:25.980 --> 44:26.500
I promise

44:26.739 --> 44:28.060
a full month of meals,

44:28.060 --> 44:28.540
deal?

44:28.819 --> 44:29.460
Just a moment.

44:31.580 --> 44:31.980
Look.

44:34.100 --> 44:35.060
A primer for you.

44:35.380 --> 44:36.139
Stay with me here.

44:39.179 --> 44:40.020
She's here!

44:40.259 --> 44:41.580
Here's some more. There you go.

44:47.299 --> 44:47.739
Good girl.

44:58.299 --> 44:59.219
I'm not here for the cat.

44:59.900 --> 45:00.819
I'm here for you.
